    <subfield code="y">00000 Negativity $\mathcal{N}$ of the Alice-Bob final state as a function of $x_A$ with the detector trajectories shown in Figure \ref{fig:stdiagram} and with the sharp switching functions~\eqref{eq:chi-sharp}, for $R=4$, $T=1.8$, $\Omega_A = \Omega_B = 1$, $\lambda_A =\lambda_B=0.01$ and $\Lambda = 10^{-2} \ll\Omega_\nu$. Before the interaction $\mathcal{N}=\frac12$, and the evolution causes the entanglement to degrade. When $x_A>T$, Alice does not cross the firewall during her detector's operation and the entanglement degradation is identical to that in Minkowski vacuum. When $x_A &amp;lt; T$, Alice does cross the firewall, and the entanglement degradation depends non-monotonically on~$x_A$.</subfield>
